{"amendments":[{"body":"`update_task_run()` no longer replays completions against legacy two-row NDJSON attempts, which breaks the backward-compatibility/repair story the new service API promises. `service.rs` says repeated terminal completions should be able to repair snapshot/journal state without duplication (`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:545-548`), but the no-`run_id` selector in `FsTaskRunLineageStore::update_task_run()` only accepts a single non-terminal match and explicitly filters out superseded legacy start rows (`src/adapters/fs.rs:2557-2577`). For existing data written by the old code, one attempt is stored as `running` + terminal rows with the same `bead_id`/`project_id` and no `run_id`, so replaying that completion now errors with \"ambiguous task run update ... provide run_id\" instead of repairing the milestone state.","rationale":"Existing milestone NDJSON is supposed to stay usable after this change. As written, old partially-failed completions cannot be recovered through the new update path."},{"body":"`record_bead_start()` is not idempotent for the same `(bead_id, project_id, run_id)`, and that can strand a run permanently once `update_task_run()` starts requiring a unique row. The start path appends a new running entry before writing snapshot/journal and allows the same bead to be started again (`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:434-472`). If the first start call fails after `append_task_run()` and the controller retries, the file now contains duplicate running rows with the same `run_id`; later, `FsTaskRunLineageStore::update_task_run()` treats multiple exact `run_id` matches as ambiguous and refuses to finalize either one (`src/adapters/fs.rs:2510-2555`). With the new in-place finalization model, a transient start-side failure can therefore make the bead impossible to complete.","rationale":"This turns a retryable partial failure into an unrecoverable state corruption for the current run, which is a hard correctness issue."}],"summary":"Reviewed the milestone-lineage changes in `model.rs`, `service.rs`, and `fs.rs`. The new fields/query coverage is mostly sound, but I found two correctness issues around retry/idempotency: one breaks repair of legacy two-row task-run records, and the other can make a run impossible to finalize after a start-side partial failure."}